The government has funded a Sh44 million water project in Pokot South constituency.MP David Pkosing said the project will benefit more than 30,000 residents in Tapach and Batei wards.He said the project will take five months to complete. Pkosing urged residents to work closely with the contractor to ensure the project is successful. Pkosing said cases of waterborne diseases have increased and that is why are investing in the project. He spoke in Sina village on Tuesday.West Pokot woman representative Regina Nyeris praised the Jubilee administration for rolling out water projects. She said the project will save women from walking long distances to look for water. Cases of mothers miscarrying are rampant, because they walk for more than 30km in search of water, Nyeris said.